descript.abstract: Hydrography map of Tutuila Island, American Samoa produced by combining four DLG shape files acquired from the USGS in March of 2001. Original DLG files were made by GEODIGITAL MAPPING, INCORPORATED in 1989 and scale = 1/24,000. Stream names were added based on a USGS topoquad that was last revised in 1987. In addition, stream orders were calculated and are included. Derived product made by the Department of Commerce, American Samoa Government.

procstep.procdesc: Four hydrographic shape files covering the island of Tutuila in American Samoa were acquired from the USGS. Using geoprocessing wizard in ArcView, shapefiles were merged into a single coverage. Position of features was shifted to the northwest as compared to NGS monument ground control points so shapefile was converted to a coverage and transformed using tic marks established in NGS monument point coverage. Coverage was converted back to a shape file and major and minor stream names were added using ArcView. Stream order numbers were also added into an 'order' attribute.

qattracc.attracce: Stream major is the name of main branch of the stream applied to all tributaries. Stream minor is the name of individual tributaries of the larger stream. If the tributaries had no name, then the name of the main branch was entered. If the stream was not labeled on the USGS topoquad, then a value of "no_name" was assigned.

Order refers to the stream order. Headwater streams were assigned a value of one (first-order streams). Stream segments below where two first-order streams come together are assigned a value of two (second-order). Stream segments below where two second-order streams come together were assigned a value of 3 and so on so forth.

attracc.attraccr: Stream name attributes taken from tif image of USGS topoquad last updated in 1987. Reading names was difficult and may have resulted in some mispellings.
